# Part 3 – Uppercase & Lowercase

```python
name = input("Enter Name: ")

print(name.upper())
```

Input

```text
Srujan
```

Output

```text
SRUJAN
```

---

Now:

```python
print(name.lower())
```

Output

```text
srujan
```

---

Why is this useful?

Suppose a user enters:

```text
Male
```

or

```text
male
```

or

```text
MALE
```

Instead of checking all three:

```python
if gender.lower() == "male":
```

Now every version becomes:

```text
male
```

Very useful.

