# Real App Connection

When users upload blood reports, OCR (Optical Character Recognition) extracts **text**, not neat data.

For example:

```text
Hemoglobin : 13.2 g/dL
HbA1c : 5.8 %
Vitamin D : 24 ng/mL
```

You'll use string methods to:

* Remove extra spaces
* Standardize capitalization
* Search for test names
* Extract values
* Clean OCR mistakes

Today's lesson is one of the foundations for processing those reports automatically.

